President Biden has declared a state of emergency in the Commonwealth of the Northern Mariana Islands due to the impacts of Tropical Storm Bolaven. This declaration allows the Federal Emergency Management Agency (FEMA) to coordinate disaster relief efforts and provide assistance to the affected areas. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment to alleviate the impacts of the emergency. Under the Public Assistance program, emergency protective measures will be provided with 75 percent federal funding. Benigno B. Ruiz has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations in the affected areas. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.